[{"id":"VH917675","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The random variable <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> can take on the values of 0, 1, 2, 3, or 4. The expected value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is 2.8. Which of the following is the best interpretation of the expected value of random variable <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH917675_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A randomly selected value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> must be equal to 2.8.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> vary by about 2.8 units from the mean of the distribution.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mean of a random sample of values selected from the distribution will be 2.8.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> randomly selected from the distribution will be less than 2.8 units of the mean.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">For values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W\"><math alttext=\"W\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>W</mi></mro